AGRO BI aims to provide real-time and ubiquitous information that traditionally requires a lot of time and resources to compile and organize, enabling faster analysis and management of KPIs in each activity through custom dashboards. AGRO BI powered by Microsoft services does not replace conventional work processes already installed, such as database-based management programs or excel files, but rather allows them to be combined and integrated into one environment and workspace.
Business Intelligence (BI) allows the collection of data and consequently their transformation into useful information and timely for decision making in areas such as purchasing and sales, operations, human resources and sustainability.
Whether on laptop or mobile phone, implementing AGRO BI will enable you to achieve three key goals these days:
 
1) better knowledge of data and organization;
2) better analysis of useful data;
3) monitoring of important indicators

The N3tSensors AGRO Platform gives you the power to have:
 - 24/7/365 Real-Time Monitoring and Control;
 - Integration of new and existing Sensors and Agricultural Systems;
 - Single Dashboard in a Web Browser (no App needed);
 - Alarms by Email, SMS and Voice;
 - Data Export.
N3tSensors AGRO is a modular software platform, accessible through a simple Internet browser, for the automation of the monitoring and control of Sensors and Agricultural Systems.
N3tSensors AGRO has the capacity to, upstream, to interact and collect data (Collector Module) from Sensors and Systems, which can be supported by various physical media and protocols, as well as, downstream, and according to the results of the data collected, act (Communicate Module) on the Devices and/or Agricultural Systems, in line with the established rules and parameters.
In addition, N3tSensors AGRO allows total independence from the Systems and Hardware of the various Manufacturers, that is, the possibility of monitoring and controlling sets of heterogeneous systems installed and/or to be installed with a single platform.

N3tSensors AGRO PLUS is the Premium version of N3tSensors AGRO.
The establish partnership between NumbersAgain and Itri Corporation (owner of Hawk-Eye™ Systems) gave us the possibility to expand our scope and advantages.
The N3tSensors AGRO PLUS Platform gives you the power to have:
 - 24/7/365 Real-Time Monitoring and Control;
 - Measurement & Listening to what the Crop has to "Say";
 - Prescribing Irrigation;
 - Remote Scouting Crop; 
 - Integration of new and existing Sensors and Agricultural Systems;
 - Dashboard in a Web Browser (no App needed);
 - Alarms by Email, SMS and Voice;
 - Data Export.
N3tSensors AGRO PLUS has the exact same features and workflow of N3tSensors AGRO with the additional integration, upstream, of the Hawk-Eye™ Systems.
The Hawk-Eye™ Systems are fully autonomous, 24/7/365, remote sensing and reporting systems that image and measures canopy temperature in the far-IR band and canopy color in the visual band from image data captured and reported every ten minutes, day and night.
From the data indices, notices, and enhanced imagery of the crop are available to certified clients in real-time via internet to phones, mobile devices, and desktops. Measurements are processed in real-time to assess and report canopy color, homogeneity, and crop stress; and to provide irrigation guidance. The indices can be formatted to actuate irrigation, fertigation, and precision applications of herbicides, pesticides and other amendments. All the imagery and data are archived for look backs and record keeping.
Hawk-Eye™ camera set is established near the crop to gain a view of the canopy. May be mounted at any point that has a view of the crop. The mobile communications send from the field to Hawk-Eye™’s cloud. Powered by DC/AC and relocated when needed.
Hawk-Eye™ System distills the extremely large amounts of data to provide pertinent and actionable real-time messages from the crop. Use it to scout for early warning of disease, pests, drainage issues, and the impact of cultivation practices. Use it to prescribe irrigation. It will recommend needed irrigation and can be tuned to provide deficit irrigation guidance.
As result of the Hawk-Eye™ System performance, part of data will be collected by N3tSensors AGRO PLUS, with which, and based on the established rules and parameters, will interact (Communicate Module) with the Devices and/or Agricultural Systems.
In parallel, N3tSensors AGRO PLUS can provide data collected from local Weather Stations.

Ekylibre offers two web-based management solutions for farms as well as a dedicated solution for large accounts:

- Clic&Farm, a free solution dedicated to plot management and traceability of crop production (mainly field crops and market gardening);
- Ekyagri, a solution which allows you to manage your entire farm in detail, from managing your production to keeping your accounting;
- Ekyviti, a solution dedicated to the management of vineyards;
- Ekyagri Premium, based on the Ekylibre software, we offer dedicated hosting and tailor-made developments to meet all your needs.

AgNav is a new sustainability toolkit that provides farmers with accurate and verifiable data to support decision making on farm to help meet agriculture’s Climate Action. It streamlines the collection of key farm data and utilises it to accurately provide baseline figures, supports farmers to use verified data, to make better decisions and implement them.
The objectives of AgNav include:
Encourage and support farmers to implement climate action and sustainability improvement on Irish farms;
Leverage the most robust inter-agency data, research and resources to drive the most appropriate actions tailored to individual farms;
Enable the most precise capture and analysis of data allowing accurate calculation of action impact;
Provide a mechanism to support the quantification of progress towards Climate Action Plan targets for the agri sector;
Support clear communications on positive progress achieved at farm level – gives control to farmers.

Because of environmental issues and in order to control the costs of their farms, farmers want to reduce their consumption of phytosanitary products. 
EcophytoPIC integrated crop protection web portal brings together all the knowledge and methods at their disposal. It as a real toolbox that contains a variety of resources: 
- information on the latest developments in integrated crop protection, with the possibility of filtering by sector;
- synthetic focus on essential technical themes;
- network resources including testimonies and videos of agricultural advisors, farmers or farms relating their experience;
- a glyphosate/herbicide resource center to accompany the exit;
- a copper resource center to accompany the reduction of copper in viticulture;
- an agenda of upcoming events and a press review.

The aim of EcophytoPIC is to raise the awareness of professionals in the agricultural sector on the subject of Integrated Crop Protection and thus to change practices towards a reduction in the use of phytopharmaceutical products.

OsareDSS is a digital service to support advisors and farmers in smart olive growing, that provides:
(i) a tool to access the data of olive fly infestation collected by local advisors;
(ii) a tool for the participatory monitoring of olive fly infestation, using a simplified method for farmers (in their own olive groves);
(iii) daily temperature and rainfall data from agrometeorological stations located in small olive farms in the South of Tuscany;
(iv) models, both using traditional techniques and Artificial Intelligence, to estimate the risk of olive fly infestation and the dynamic of infestation (e.g., phenology and mortality of olive fly);
(v) “Aeco DSS”, a decision support system which elaborate balances to define optimal irrigations and fertilizations (nitrogen, phosphorus and potassium). Aeco allows the user to create and save farm centres and fields. In each field it is possible to enter soil characteristics, management practices useful for the soil nutrient balance and crop information, such as the expected yield.

OsareDSS is available both as a web site and as an app.

The DATs work as a platform based on MOODLE. It is used to:
- Improve the availability and quality of advisory services to farmers;
- Expert content of public agricultural advisory service of all fields of farming, collected in one place;
- Use of advanced educational methods - implementation of interactive trainings;
- The possibility of obtaining a certificate of participation in education;
- The possibility of easy communication between the farmer and the advisor (via text or video);
o More effective transfer of knowledge from consultant to farmer and specialist consultant to field consultant;

The Strategic Management Tool (SMT) in an internet tool to implement the method of Interactive Strategic Management (ISM). In this method, the notion of ‘strategy’ is central. A strategy determines the way the user will reach his goals. SMT contains three pre-defined market strategies and eight farm development strategies.
The tool contains the following chapters which the user has to fill in digitally:
1.	Enterprise;
2.	Environment (external factors);
3.	Entrepreneur;
4.	Mission, Vision, Goals;
5.	Strategies;
6.	Critical success factors;
7.	Plan of action.

With the answers given by the user, the tool calculates scores for the first three chapters. In chapter 5,  the user can select goal strategies, based on his mission, vision and goals (chapter 4). The tool compares these selected strategies with the scores of each of the strategies in the tool and gives insight in the central question: ‘Which strategy is the most suitable for me and my enterprise given the environment of my enterprise?’ This comparison includes a gap analysis, indicating to which extent a certain strategy does or does not fit with the specific combination of enterprise, environment and entrepreneur.

When the best strategy is assessed, the user defines critical success factors (chapter 6) and a plan of action (chapter 7). He can start to implement his plan immediately after the group training in which SMT is filled in and the results are discussed. The critical success factors help him to monitor his progress.

EcceOlio is a digital service composed by an app and a website aimed at:
(i) supporting the promotion of innovations for increasing the sustainability in the control of olive fly (e.g., conservation biological control);
(ii) supporting farms in marketing through the valorisation and the dissemination of the characteristics of farms managing their olive groves with sustainable practices.

EcceOlio supports the monitoring of olive fly infestation and the visualization of the data in the website.

The app allows farmers to enter data about their farm in four main sessions:
(i) farm data: main farm data, including for example localization, email, social accounts, pictures;
(ii) productivity data: e.g., cultivated olive varieties, packaging, type of oil, selling methodology, possibility of testing on the farm;
(iii) sustainability of olive growing: checklist for the auto evaluation of the level of sustainability of olive growing in the farm;
(iv) oil quality: data on chemical and sensory properties of the produced oil.

In the website all the registered farms are visible in a map. For each farm it is possible to visualize the data inserted through the app and at each farm is assigned a QR code usable for marketing purposes.

Through an in-depth analysis of the farm, farmer and environment, the SMT tool shows the farmer the best possibilities, suitable for him and his farm and helps him prepare a farm development strategy - the farmer learns which farming strategy is most suitable for him and how he can implement it (additional support: the analysis and reflection with other farmers in the group and advisor/s)
Main purpose of SMT (Strategic Management Tool):
- Assistance in deciding on the direction of farming (young farmers) - better decisions -> economically more successful farms (a good plan is the basis);
- Help to understand why the current direction of farming is not successful enough and what and how to change;
- Development of the idea how to make a successful farm even more successful.

